02:09.496 --> 02:12.363
(line ringing)
(sighs)

02:12.365 --> 02:14.332
Hello, Rajesh.
How are things by you?

02:14.334 --> 02:15.433
Good, good.

02:15.435 --> 02:17.602
Uh, listen,
I just wanted to let you know

02:17.604 --> 02:19.103
when you get
my credit card bill,

02:19.105 --> 02:21.005
it might be a little high
this month.

02:21.007 --> 02:23.274
Well, you're a grown man
with a steady job.

02:23.276 --> 02:27.045
Why wouldn't you spend
all your father's money?

02:27.047 --> 02:31.382
(chuckling): Oh, Daddy,
you're so rich and funny.

02:31.384 --> 02:34.552
Yeah. So what else is going on
with your life?

02:34.554 --> 02:37.689
Uh, well, I was dating a woman
at the university,

02:37.691 --> 02:39.057
but we broke up.

02:39.059 --> 02:40.959
I'm sorry to hear that.

02:40.961 --> 02:44.028
I know you are. That's why
you just bought me a new iPad.

02:45.465 --> 02:46.764
And before you start,

02:46.766 --> 02:49.834
I am not interested in
you arranging a marriage for me.

02:49.836 --> 02:52.236
Oh, I gave up on that
a long time ago.

02:52.238 --> 02:53.304
You did?

02:53.306 --> 02:54.672
It's too much work.

02:54.674 --> 02:56.107
You're an adult who can't get by

02:56.109 --> 02:58.176
without an allowance
from his parents.

02:58.178 --> 02:59.844
Women don't want that.

02:59.846 --> 03:03.014
Wh-What are you saying,
that y-you're giving up on me?

03:03.016 --> 03:05.283
What kind of father gives up
on his son?

03:05.285 --> 03:06.584
I have six children,

03:06.586 --> 03:08.886
five of whom are married
and self-sufficient.

03:08.888 --> 03:12.323
I don't think I'm the problem.

03:13.193 --> 03:14.859
I can't believe
what I'm hearing.

03:14.861 --> 03:17.295
This is deeply hurtful.

03:17.297 --> 03:18.363
You're also too sensitive.

03:18.365 --> 03:21.132
Women don't want that either.

03:24.537 --> 03:26.270
The food here's
supposed to be great.

03:26.272 --> 03:27.638
Don't fill up
on chips.

03:27.640 --> 03:29.374
Oh, I won't.
I have a trick.

03:29.376 --> 03:31.976
I only eat
equilateral triangles.

03:33.179 --> 03:35.880
Isosceles, isosceles,

03:35.882 --> 03:38.483
oh, scalene...

03:39.319 --> 03:41.519
You didn't see that.

03:42.722 --> 03:44.455
Oh, look.

03:44.457 --> 03:45.823
It's Bert, at the bar.

03:45.825 --> 03:47.325
We should
go say hi.

03:47.327 --> 03:49.794
Why?

03:49.796 --> 03:51.729
Because that's what you do

03:51.731 --> 03:54.632
when you see someone you know
in a public place.

03:54.634 --> 03:58.803
I have multiple restraining
orders that say otherwise.

04:00.473 --> 04:03.241
Sheldon, there's a difference
between greeting a friend

04:03.243 --> 04:05.610
and following a celebrity
into a bathroom.

04:06.813 --> 04:08.613
If the judge
couldn't explain it to me,

04:08.615 --> 04:10.815
I don't see how you will.

04:12.852 --> 04:14.552
Hi, Bert.
Hello.

04:14.554 --> 04:16.019
Oh, hey, guys.

04:16.022 --> 04:17.088
What brings you here?

04:17.089 --> 04:19.123
Oh, we're having date night.
Nice.

04:19.125 --> 04:20.524
I'm meeting someone, too.

04:20.527 --> 04:22.060
Oh, really. Anybody we know?

04:22.062 --> 04:25.096
I doubt it. I met
her on G-Harmony.

04:25.098 --> 04:28.766
That's a Web site for
geologists to find love.

04:28.768 --> 04:30.501
That's a real thing?

04:30.503 --> 04:33.604
Yeah. Their slogan is
“We're all about dating

04:33.606 --> 04:36.107
and not the carbon-14 kind”"

04:37.911 --> 04:40.211
Well, have
a lovely evening.

04:40.213 --> 04:42.080
Thanks. You, too.

04:43.149 --> 04:44.615
If you think
that's more fun than talking

04:44.617 --> 04:47.051
to Zachary Quinto through
a stall door, you're crazy.

04:50.056 --> 04:51.355
You know, we could've come
to you guys.

04:51.357 --> 04:52.890
You didn't have to bring
the baby here.

04:52.892 --> 04:54.559
Oh, it's okay. It's good
to get out of the house.

04:54.561 --> 04:56.094
And the car ride
puts her to sleep.

04:56.096 --> 04:58.629
Aw, that used to work
with Sheldon.

04:58.631 --> 05:01.999
Yeah, until someone left him
in the drugstore parking lot

05:02.001 --> 05:03.367
and he freaked out.

05:03.369 --> 05:05.036
Who forgot to crack the window?

05:05.805 --> 05:07.071
Hello!

05:07.073 --> 05:08.372
LEONARD: Hey.
PENNY: Oh,

05:08.374 --> 05:09.874
someone's been shopping
at Gucci.

05:09.876 --> 05:12.743
Yeah, I saw something for Halley
and I couldn't resist.

05:12.745 --> 05:14.579
That's so
sweet of you.

05:14.581 --> 05:18.416
Yeah, it's a crushed velvet
baby cape.

05:19.486 --> 05:22.987
Oh, no, now we have two.

05:23.890 --> 05:26.124
That must've been expensive.
Yeah, it was.

05:26.126 --> 05:29.360
But it's my father's money
and I'm mad at him.

05:30.530 --> 05:31.496
What's going on with your dad?

05:31.498 --> 05:32.697
And if you really want
to hurt him,

05:32.699 --> 05:34.432
I look great in Chanel.
(clears throat)

05:34.434 --> 05:38.069
It turns out he doesn't care
if I'm married or if I'm single.

05:38.071 --> 05:39.904
He's basically given up on me.

05:39.906 --> 05:41.973
Oh, I'm sure that's not true.

05:41.975 --> 05:44.876
It is. He stopped trying to find
Indian girls for me to marry.

05:44.878 --> 05:47.111
All you did was complain
when he did that.

05:47.113 --> 05:50.081
Leonard, he's hurting.
Let him feel how he feels.

05:50.083 --> 05:51.883
Thank you, Penny.
Yeah.

05:51.885 --> 05:54.018
Shoes, I'm a seven-and-a-half;
boots, I'm an eight.

05:56.856 --> 05:59.056
...MSN Search,

05:59.058 --> 06:01.058
AltaVista,

06:01.060 --> 06:04.061
and... Ask Jeeves.

06:04.063 --> 06:05.396
You?

06:05.398 --> 06:06.998
Sorry, I don't have a list

06:07.000 --> 06:09.667
of defunct search engines
that I miss.

06:11.604 --> 06:13.437
Hey. Looks like I got stood up,

06:13.439 --> 06:14.972
so I'm gonna head out.

06:14.974 --> 06:16.474
Oh, no. Are you sure
you don't want to give her

06:16.476 --> 06:17.542
a few more minutes?

06:17.544 --> 06:20.645
Nah, G-Harmony recommends
after two hours,

06:20.647 --> 06:23.681
it's time to cut bait.

06:25.585 --> 06:26.517
I'm so sorry.

06:26.519 --> 06:29.253
Bert, I insist
that you join us.

06:29.255 --> 06:31.122
You really wouldn't mind?

06:31.124 --> 06:32.690
Not at all. Amy?

06:32.692 --> 06:33.958
Fine with me.

06:33.960 --> 06:36.460
Thanks. I'll go grab a chair.

06:36.462 --> 06:39.664
Sheldon, that was so sweet
of you.

06:39.666 --> 06:41.866
Well, I could deduce
by his facial expression

06:41.868 --> 06:44.068
and body language
that he was sad.

06:44.070 --> 06:48.339
So the part where he got
stood up didn't clue you in?

06:48.341 --> 06:53.344
You want me to look at him
<i>and</i> listen to him?

06:54.547 --> 06:57.715
My father thinks the reason
I can't make a relationship work

06:57.717 --> 06:59.383
is because I'm spoiled.

07:04.490 --> 07:08.059
I'm sorry, is he waiting
for someone to disagree?

07:08.061 --> 07:09.994
Just because he helps me out

07:09.996 --> 07:12.730
doesn't automatically mean
that I'm spoiled.

07:12.732 --> 07:14.452
All right, how much exactly
does he pay for?

07:16.035 --> 07:18.035
Okay,
I'll tell you,

07:18.037 --> 07:19.503
but please don't judge me.

07:19.505 --> 07:23.474
He pays for my car, my rent,
and my credit cards.

07:25.778 --> 07:28.579
I'm trying, but I'm judging.

07:29.616 --> 07:32.083
Maybe your dad's right.

07:32.085 --> 07:34.418
Yeah, women do like a man
that can support himself.

07:34.420 --> 07:36.020
But Bernadette makes
more money than Howard.

07:36.022 --> 07:39.156
She basically
supports him.

07:39.158 --> 07:41.759
Yeah, maybe your
dad's right.

07:44.631 --> 07:47.531
Good question. Let's see.

07:47.533 --> 07:49.400
Infoseek,

07:49.402 --> 07:51.269
WebCrawler,

07:51.271 --> 07:53.170
oh, HotBot.

07:53.172 --> 07:55.906
Okay, literally
any other topic.

07:56.676 --> 07:59.844
All right.
How did you guys meet?

07:59.846 --> 08:02.013
Actually, we met online.

08:02.015 --> 08:04.015
Our-our first date
was at a coffee shop.

08:04.017 --> 08:07.084
Although, unlike your date,
she actually showed up.

08:08.388 --> 08:10.454
Oh, he looks sad again.

08:11.324 --> 08:14.358
Well, I really envy
your relationship.

08:14.360 --> 08:16.927
Other than you two only
having sex once a year,

08:16.929 --> 08:19.530
you're the perfect couple.

08:21.034 --> 08:22.967
You-you know about that?

08:22.969 --> 08:26.170
Uh, yeah, everyone at
the university does.

08:26.172 --> 08:28.306
Were you aware of this?

08:28.308 --> 08:32.342
No. No, I only told Leonard,
Howard, Raj,

08:32.345 --> 08:35.613
Kripke, uh, Professor Wu,
Professor Klein,

08:35.615 --> 08:38.582
and a lunch lady
in the cafeteria.

08:38.583 --> 08:42.019
How everyone else found out
is a mystery to me.

