08:52.563 --> 08:54.630
Why aren't you
talking to me?

08:54.632 --> 08:56.632
- Because I'm mad at you.
- Oh.

08:56.634 --> 08:59.935
Well, now I'm sorry I asked.

08:59.937 --> 09:01.870
Sheldon, it's humiliating.

09:01.872 --> 09:05.040
Thanks to you, my colleagues are
gossiping about our sex life.

09:05.042 --> 09:06.542
What is there to gossip about?

09:06.544 --> 09:08.877
We barely have one.

09:09.714 --> 09:12.414
That's why they're doing it!

09:15.619 --> 09:19.455
Is it safe to assume
you're not speaking to me again?

09:20.725 --> 09:23.392
If you're not answering because
you're not speaking to me,

09:23.394 --> 09:25.294
perhaps we could come up
with a signal!

09:25.296 --> 09:27.496
(door slams)

09:30.267 --> 09:31.967
That works!

09:34.505 --> 09:36.004
You don't need your dad's money.

09:36.006 --> 09:38.307
You can get by on your salary.
LEONARD: Yeah.

09:38.309 --> 09:40.476
Well, we work at the
same place as you, and

09:40.478 --> 09:42.077
we've always been fine.
KOOTHRAPPALI: Oh, please.

09:42.079 --> 09:45.414
Look in the mirror. You both
look ten years older than I do.

09:46.250 --> 09:48.016
PENNY:
All right.

09:48.018 --> 09:49.351
Hang on. We can
figure this out.

09:49.353 --> 09:52.020
Let's just go over your
expenses. How much is your rent?

09:52.022 --> 09:53.856
I don't want to say.

09:53.858 --> 09:56.058
Is it really
that high?

09:56.060 --> 09:59.361
I don't want to say because
I don't know how much it is.

09:59.363 --> 10:01.663
You don't how much
your rent is?

10:01.665 --> 10:03.557
My father pays for it! Do you
know how much your rent is?!

10:03.581 --> 10:04.534
Yeah.

10:04.535 --> 10:05.834
Well, then double it,

10:05.836 --> 10:07.870
because my building's
a lot nicer than this dump.

10:09.006 --> 10:12.007
Do you know how
much your car costs?

10:12.009 --> 10:13.075
Not really.

10:13.077 --> 10:15.110
Well, how much
do you spend on food?

10:15.112 --> 10:18.147
The housekeeper
does the shopping.

10:18.983 --> 10:21.717
Oh, my God, you
really are spoiled.

10:21.719 --> 10:23.018
<i>I'm</i> spoiled?!

10:23.020 --> 10:26.722
Your baby has a cape
that costs $300!

10:32.329 --> 10:33.428
I'm going to bed.

10:33.430 --> 10:34.930
Well, wait.

10:34.932 --> 10:38.767
This is our first fight as
a couple who live together.

10:38.769 --> 10:40.035
So?

10:40.037 --> 10:42.304
I'm not sure of the protocol.

10:42.306 --> 10:43.605
Television teaches us

10:43.607 --> 10:45.207
that the man's supposed
to sleep on the couch,

10:45.209 --> 10:48.844
but of the two of us,
you're clearly more sofa-sized.

10:48.846 --> 10:50.712
I'm not sleeping on the couch

10:50.714 --> 10:53.115
'cause you don't know
what's private and what's not.

10:53.117 --> 10:55.150
This isn't fair.

10:55.152 --> 10:56.518
You've discussed aspects

10:56.520 --> 10:58.353
of our physical relationship
with Penny.

10:58.355 --> 10:59.788
That's different!

10:59.790 --> 11:02.357
She's a close friend,
not the lady in the cafeteria

11:02.359 --> 11:05.194
who cuts the crust off
your sandwiches!

11:05.196 --> 11:06.795
That lady has a name.

11:06.797 --> 11:08.330
I don't know what it is,

11:08.332 --> 11:10.732
but one time,
I accidentally called her “Mom”.

11:13.971 --> 11:16.371
Sounds like you're gonna
need a cheaper place to live.

11:16.373 --> 11:18.540
When you moved here,
you didn't have a lot of money.

11:18.542 --> 11:19.608
How'd you get by?

11:19.610 --> 11:21.743
Well, sometimes
you can get free food

11:21.745 --> 11:24.613
and Wi-Fi from the neighbors.

11:24.615 --> 11:26.081
Just know

11:26.083 --> 11:29.151
you might have
to marry one of 'em.

11:30.120 --> 11:31.720
Hey, you guys let Stuart
live with you.

11:31.722 --> 11:32.888
Why not Raj, too?

11:32.890 --> 11:35.557
What-what are you doing? I...

11:37.094 --> 11:40.162
I-I-I schlepped the baby over,
I brought imported beer.

11:40.164 --> 11:42.064
Why don't you like me?

11:42.066 --> 11:43.165
KOOTHRAPPALI:
Well,

11:43.167 --> 11:44.486
I thought
we were best friends!

11:44.510 --> 11:45.501
We are!

11:45.502 --> 11:49.037
That's why I'm sad my best
friend's gonna be homeless.

11:51.175 --> 11:54.276
I'm sorry, Raj. We really
just don't have the space.

11:54.278 --> 11:55.677
What if he lives in your garage?

11:55.679 --> 11:58.013
What if you stop helping?!

11:59.383 --> 12:02.217
Guys, I'm not living
in a garage!

12:02.219 --> 12:04.353
Wait. Why are we talking
about our place

12:04.355 --> 12:08.123
when Sheldon's old room is
sitting there perfectly empty?

12:10.261 --> 12:12.027
That's a great idea.

12:12.029 --> 12:14.463
Raj,

12:14.465 --> 12:17.699
if you need a place to stay,
of course you are welcome here.

12:17.701 --> 12:21.870
Thank you, but if I'm gonna just
take advantage of my friends,

12:21.872 --> 12:24.706
I might as well keep on
relying on my father.

12:24.708 --> 12:26.108
Okay, only if you're sure.

12:26.110 --> 12:27.476
(quietly):
Whew.

12:27.478 --> 12:29.878
Yeah.

12:30.981 --> 12:32.981
(knocking)
SHELDON: Amy?

12:32.983 --> 12:34.249
(knocking)
Amy?

12:34.251 --> 12:36.585
(knocking) Amy?
Yeah?

12:37.621 --> 12:40.389
Not exactly the welcome wagon,
but I'll take it.

12:42.326 --> 12:44.459
What is this?

12:44.461 --> 12:47.296
I'm mapping basic topics
of conversation

12:47.298 --> 12:49.998
and with whom
they can be discussed.

12:50.000 --> 12:54.369
I call these circles
“Zones of Privacy”"

12:54.371 --> 12:55.637
Don't Google that

12:55.639 --> 12:58.106
unless you want to see pictures
of people's genitals.

12:58.108 --> 13:01.843
This circle contains
only me and you.

13:01.845 --> 13:04.713
It represents subjects we
only share with each other...

13:04.715 --> 13:08.550
details of physical intimacy,
bathroom habits.

13:08.552 --> 13:10.385
Although, as I'm saying it,

13:10.387 --> 13:14.289
I may need
to add Dr. Fink in here.

13:14.291 --> 13:15.691
Are you really worried

13:15.693 --> 13:18.026
about revealing secrets
to Stephen Hawking?

13:18.028 --> 13:22.664
No, I was just excited
to list him as a friend.

13:22.666 --> 13:25.901
Well, I do appreciate
you working on this.

13:27.671 --> 13:29.571
I'm sorry you were embarrassed.

13:29.573 --> 13:31.440
And now I understand that

13:31.442 --> 13:33.775
some things are just
between you and me,

13:33.777 --> 13:38.280
and in the event of redness
and swelling, Dr. Fink.

13:40.584 --> 13:42.384
What's that little dot
in the middle?

13:42.386 --> 13:45.620
That's reserved for thoughts
I don't share with anyone.

13:45.622 --> 13:49.925
Interesting. You really
have secrets you don't tell me?

13:49.927 --> 13:51.493
Of course.

13:51.495 --> 13:53.195
Can I hear one?

13:53.197 --> 13:55.230
No, they're private.

13:55.232 --> 13:59.134
Why? Are they naughty?

13:59.970 --> 14:02.170
A little.

14:02.172 --> 14:03.839
Please?

14:03.841 --> 14:06.041
Fine.

14:07.211 --> 14:09.378
Two years ago...

14:10.581 --> 14:13.281
...I got my driver's license.

14:14.118 --> 14:16.551
What?!

14:17.821 --> 14:19.821
Why didn't
you say anything?!

14:19.823 --> 14:23.225
I like being
chauffeured around.

14:23.227 --> 14:25.827
It makes me feel important.

14:27.464 --> 14:30.532
So when I got up at 4:00 a.m.
to drive you across the desert

14:30.534 --> 14:33.468
to an antique train museum,
I didn't have to?

14:33.470 --> 14:34.736
No, you didn't.

14:34.738 --> 14:36.538
But keep in mind,

14:36.540 --> 14:39.708
I felt extremely important.

14:42.012 --> 14:44.212
(line ringing)

14:44.214 --> 14:45.514
(beep)

14:45.516 --> 14:48.016
What?!

14:48.018 --> 14:49.251
Hello, Father.

14:49.253 --> 14:50.519
We need to talk.

14:50.521 --> 14:51.920
All right.

14:51.922 --> 14:53.655
I have come
to an important decision.

14:53.657 --> 14:55.490
I will not be accepting
your money anymore.

14:55.492 --> 14:58.226
I'm a man,
and I can take care of myself.

14:58.228 --> 14:59.895
That's wonderful!

14:59.897 --> 15:01.196
Yes, that is wonderful!

15:01.198 --> 15:03.398
You will no longer be able
to accuse me of being spoiled!

15:03.400 --> 15:05.300
I am so proud of you.

15:05.302 --> 15:06.535
Dad, I'm trying to tell you off,

15:06.537 --> 15:09.438
and you're ruining it
with your delight and relief.

15:10.841 --> 15:12.274
Sorry.

15:12.276 --> 15:15.410
Oh, no, my grown son is going
to stop spending all my money.

15:15.412 --> 15:18.346
Where did I fail as a father?!

15:18.348 --> 15:20.382
Yeah, that's right.

15:20.384 --> 15:21.917
Keep asking yourself that!

15:23.153 --> 15:26.688
But I still love you very much,
so don't cut me out of the will.

15:35.163 --> 15:36.596
Oh, you brought
your own lunch.

15:36.598 --> 15:37.764
Good for you.

15:37.766 --> 15:39.899
Yeah, I'm making a bunch
of changes.

15:39.901 --> 15:42.068
This morning,
I fired my dog walker.

15:42.070 --> 15:44.471
Oh. How's the dog gonna go
to the bathroom?

15:44.473 --> 15:46.039
Uh, I gave her an Imodium.

15:46.041 --> 15:47.807
That's tomorrow's problem.

15:49.578 --> 15:52.712
Excuse me. May I have
your attention, please?

15:52.714 --> 15:54.247
I have recently

15:54.249 --> 15:57.017
been made aware
that my personal relationship

15:57.019 --> 16:00.220
with Amy Farrah Fowler has
become water cooler gossip.

16:00.222 --> 16:04.124
And I just want to say,
shame on all of you.

16:05.160 --> 16:06.793
We're scientists.

16:06.795 --> 16:08.061
Our minds should be focused

16:08.063 --> 16:10.530
on the advancement
of human knowledge,

16:10.532 --> 16:13.033
not the intimate details
of other people's lives.

16:13.035 --> 16:15.568
He's right.

16:15.570 --> 16:18.138
And I'm sorry for the part
I played in this.

16:18.140 --> 16:19.839
Thank you, Bert.

16:19.841 --> 16:22.942
You're a good man. That
woman who stood you up

16:22.944 --> 16:25.512
and humiliated you last
night really missed out.

16:26.915 --> 16:30.183
That doesn't paint me
in the best light.

16:30.185 --> 16:32.285
Oh. Oh, I'm sorry.

16:32.287 --> 16:37.390
Correction: That woman not only
had vigorous coitus with Bert...

16:37.392 --> 16:41.528
she also tipped him a
dollar for a job well done.

16:44.266 --> 16:46.700
- That better?
- Not really.

16:48.303 --> 16:51.338
All right, well, to sum up...
focus on science,

16:51.340 --> 16:53.573
keep your nose out
of other people's business,

16:53.575 --> 16:56.343
and, uh, whoa,
for a good time, call Bert.

17:03.518 --> 17:05.551
What brought that on?

17:05.554 --> 17:07.954
(sighs)
Well, last night Amy was angry

17:07.955 --> 17:10.457
with me because I'd been
foolishly telling people

17:10.459 --> 17:12.325
about certain personal matters.

17:12.327 --> 17:14.094
That's understandable.

17:14.096 --> 17:15.561
Oh, I know that now.

17:15.564 --> 17:17.430
At first, I thought
she was cranky

17:17.432 --> 17:19.898
because of her horrific
menstrual cramps, but...

17:20.868 --> 17:23.569
...it turns out, no, she
was genuinely mortified.

